text: Jayde Andrew Julius (born 27 August 1993 in Bellville) is a South African cyclist, who currently rides for UCI Continental team . ==Major results== ;2011 : 2nd Remouchamps–Ferrières–Remouchamps ;2015 : 1st 20px Road race, National Under-23 Road Championships : 3rd Road race, National Road Championships : 7th Road race, African Road Championships ;2016 : 5th Road race, National Road Championships ;2018 : 2nd Overall Tour de Limpopo ::1st Stage 4 (TTT) : 2nd 100 Cycle Challenge : 4th Time trial, National Road Championships ;2019 : 1st 100 Cycle Challenge : 1st Trophée Princier, Challenge du Prince : 5th Time trial, National Road Championships : 8th Road race, African Road Championships : 10th Overall Tour de Limpopo ==References== ==External links== * Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:South African male cyclists Category:Competitors at the 2019 African Games
title: Jayde Julius
